tvshowdetails.label: Justified
tvshowdetails.plot: A character drama based on the 2001 Elmore Leonard short story "Fire in the Hole." Leonard's tale centers around U.S. Marshal Raylan Givens of Kentucky, a quiet but strong-willed official of the law. The tale covers his high-stakes job, as well as his strained relationships with his ex-wife and father.
tvshowdetails.title: Justified

2.label: 2x01. The Moonshine War
2.plot: Raylan tangles with a ruthless Harlan County crime family while hunting for a fugitive sex offender.
2.title: The Moonshine War

2.label: 2x02. The Life Inside
2.plot: Raylan chases a pregnant fugitive who has fallen into the hands of human traffickers.
2.title: The Life Inside

2.label: 2x03. The I of the Storm
2.plot: The hijacking of a bus full of drugs ends in murder, and Raylan pursues the likely culprit: Boyd Crowder.
2.title: The I of the Storm

2.label: 2x04. For Blood or Money
2.plot: When Rachel's brother-in-law makes a violent escape from a halfway house, Raylan is forced to hunt him down. Boyd entertains a dangerous offer in Harlan.
2.title: For Blood or Money

2.label: 2x05. Cottonmouth
2.plot: Raylan's hunt for a killer puts him on a collision course with the Bennett clan, while Boyd plots a heist with treacherous new partners.
2.title: Cottonmouth

2.label: 2x06. Blaze of Glory
2.plot: When a terminally ill ex-con is linked to a bank heist, Art and Raylan must find him before he and his young henchmen can strike again. However, the manhunt is complicated when Winona worries that a hundred-dollar bill she took from an evidence room locker will be traced back to her after it is taken in the robbery.
2.title: Blaze of Glory

2.label: 2x07. Save My Love
2.plot: Winona's blunder could put her behind bars, unless Raylan can weave his way through a federal courthouse locked down over death threats.
2.title: Save My Love

2.label: 2x08. The Spoil
2.plot: Raylan must protect a cunning coal executive who is out of her element when negotiating with the powerful Bennett clan.
2.title: The Spoil

2.label: 2x09. Brother's Keeper
2.plot: Just as the bad blood between the Bennetts and the coal company threatens to boil over, Raylan must thwart one of Mags' sons.
2.title: Brother's Keeper

2.label: 2x10. Debts and Accounts
2.plot: Raylan and Winona's idyll is shattered by violence, as Boyd and the Bennetts struggle to rise from the ashes of chaos in Harlan.
2.title: Debts and Accounts

2.label: 2x11. Full Commitment
2.plot: Raylan realizes he wasn't the sole target of an attempted assassination, and confronts the unlikely culprit once and for all.
2.title: Full Commitment

2.label: 2x12. Reckoning
2.plot: A deadly home invasion hits Raylan personally, placing him in a race with Boyd and Arlo to find the killer. Mags is forced to make decisions about her involvement in the Bennett family's criminal activities and the fate of Dickie, who has a deadly plan to absolve himself of responsibility.
2.title: Reckoning

2.label: 2x13. Bloody Harlan
2.plot: The Crowder and the Bennett clans go to war over control of Harlan, a move that leaves dead and dying on both sides.
2.title: Bloody Harlan

4.label: 4x01. Hole in the Wall
4.plot: Raylan turns to affable but inexperienced Constable Bob for help securing a bail jumper from Tennessee, and finds evidence his family is at the center of a legendary unsolved mystery.
4.title: Hole in the Wall

4.label: 4x02. Where's Waldo?
4.plot: As Raylan tangles with a dangerous family keeping a dark secret, Boyd takes on a snake-handling preacher.
4.title: Where's Waldo?

4.label: 4x03. Truth and Consequences
4.plot: Drew Thompson's widow turns up and gets Raylan in hot water with the FBI, while Boyd's strike at the snake church is met with a surprising strike back.
4.title: Truth and Consequences
